<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:40AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Hartley
County through 515 AM CDT...
At 440 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Romero, or 12 miles northeast of Nara Visa, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Romero.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
